Maite Nkoana-Mashabane is in Angola for a meeting on peace, stability and co-operation in the DRC. JOHANNESBURG - International Relations Minister Maite Nkoana-Mashabane is currently leading a South African delegation in Angola, at a meeting on peace, stability and co-operation in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC). Minister Nkoana-Mashabane has arrived in Luanda, Angola for a regional meeting on peace in the Democratic Republic of Congo. pic.twitter.com/NUtVj9vRnz&mdash; DIRCO South Africa (@DIRCO_ZA) October 25, 2016 Minister Nkoana-Mashabane has arrived in Luanda, Angola for a regional meeting on peace in the Democratic Republic of Congo. pic.twitter.com/NUtVj9vRnz Several African countries, are expected to assess the progress made in the implementation of peace, security and cooperation framework for the DRC and the region between the eleven countries, where President Joseph Kabila will be expected to brief participating leaders on the political and security developments in the DRC.